  "closed_at": "2016-12-08T03:58:27Z",
  "body": "See the example below:\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<template>\r\n  <div style=\"color:blue\">\r\n    <text>blue</text>\r\n  </div>\r\n</template>\r\n```\r\nThe text color should be blue, but it shows black on the phone. ([demo](http://dotwe.org/8216e8160b41b588dcf26dafdf6346bc))\r\n\r\nI think we should support the inheritance, which is a useful and powerful technique in writing styles.\r\n\r\n## Properties we should support\r\n\r\nThe full list of inherited properties could be found in [W3C's spec](https://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/propidx.html). Here is a summary on stackoverflow: [Which CSS properties are inherited?](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5612302).\r\n\r\nBut we do not need to support all Inheritable properties (many properties are not support originally).\r\n\r\nHere is a candidate list I organized:\r\n\r\n+ color\r\n+ font-family\r\n+ font-size\r\n+ font-style\r\n+ font-weight\r\n+ line-height\r\n+ text-align\r\n\r\nQuite a short list.\r\n\r\nThe most important property we should support at first is **`color`** and **`font-size`**.\r\n",
